Number = {1},
Pages = {39-45},
Abstract = {S. calcaratum R. Br. (n = 11) and S. ecorne (F. Muell. ex Erickson and
   Willis) comb. et stat. nov. (S. calcaratum R. Br. var ecorne F. Muell.
   ex Erickson and Willis, n = 13) are distinct species separated by
   chromosomal, morphological and reproductive discontinuities. The derived
   species, S. calcaratum, is distributed over a wider, often more arid,
   array of ecological conditions. It exhibits a reduced interpopulational
   coadaptation indicated by low seed set following interpopulational cross
   pollinations.},
